23/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Top Serbian and Serbia-Montenegro officials will meet on Tuesday (24 May) to discuss a joint platform regarding Kosovo, the Serbian government announced. 
The document would then be presented to the UN Security Council during its meeting in New York on 27 May. 
Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Kosumi said Saturday that he would not attend the Security Council session, hinting he is unhappy with his observer status. 
(PBS BiH - 22/05/05; Beta - 21/05/05; Beta - 20/05/05)
